<section xml:id="initialize-empty-fapolicyd-database">
  <title>Initialize empty fapolicyd database</title>
  <para>
    The fapolicyd trust database is created when it runs the first time.
    In some cases, especially in testing scenarios, it is useful to
    start fapolicyd with a limited set of trust in the database. In
    other instances, like when executing our GUI application, itâ€™s good
    to be able to create the database on demand perhaps before fapolicyd
    starts.
  </para>
</section>
<section xml:id="graphical-recursive-directory-add">
  <title>Graphical recursive directory add</title>
  <para>
    Adding hierarchical directories to the trust database via a
    graphical file tree selection mechanism allows for fast recursion to
    select the entries that should be added. Filtering the tree view by
    file name and type would also be beneficial.
  </para>
</section>
<section xml:id="log-analysis">
  <title>Log analysis</title>
  <para>
    Intelligent parsing and pattern recognition within log messages
    similar to a <quote>clippy</quote> capability that can point out
    errors or suggestions about trust or rules.
  </para>
</section>
